cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.CV 

This paper discusses the vulnerabilities and countermeasures for adversarial attacks on Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the potential applications of DRL in systems such as traffic controls and autonomous vehicles, which suggests the possibility of it belonging to cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of DRL in computer vision tasks, indicating a potential connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
